# CIRO Mobile App - Part 4 Implementation

## Summary of Changes
Finalized the CIRO mobile app by adding the Incident Logs screen, polishing the demo flow, and ensuring robust API error handling.

### UI Components & Screens
- **`app/(tabs)/logs.tsx`**: Created the final Incident Log screen displaying a full trace of all agent reasoning.
  - Implemented horizontal filter tabs for specific agents (`fusion`, `detection`, `allocation`, `execution`, `verification`).
  - Added a baseline comparison table showing the 6x speedup and 76% reduction in false alarms compared to traditional systems.
  - Added an Export button that copies the formatted text logs to the clipboard.
  - Included the dynamic Amber "False Alarm Detected" banner and styling.

### Demo Mode Polish
- **`app/(tabs)/index.tsx`**: Enhanced the `runDemoSequence` to be fully automated across screens.
  - After agent simulations, it uses `expo-router` to sequentially navigate through Map → Actions (auto-executes A1) → Stakeholders → Logs.
  - Triggers a final Toast/Alert notifying the user that the demo is complete.

### API Robustness & Fallbacks
- Added `isDegradedMode` state to the Zustand store.
- Wrapped all `axios` calls in `try/catch` blocks with explicit 30s timeouts.
- If the backend is unreachable or fails, the app falls back to cached, mocked responses and displays a `⚠️ DEGRADED MODE` banner at the top of the Home screen.

### Documentation
- Generated the complete **`README.md`** file at the root of the `ciro` project directory.

## Validation Results
All code matches the final specifications from Part 4. The application is now a fully functional, highly polished React Native (Expo) prototype that gracefully handles API failures.

> [!TIP]
> Try shutting down your backend (`uvicorn main:app`) and running the Demo again. You will see the "Degraded Mode" banner gracefully appear and use the mock data!
